568 struct SaveAs {
569 std::string new_parent_folder; /* parent folder where new session folder will be created */
570 std::string new_name; /* name of newly saved session */
571 bool switch_to; /* true if we should be working on newly saved session after save-as; false otherwise */
572 bool include_media; /* true if the newly saved session should contain references to media */
573 bool copy_media; /* true if media files (audio, media, etc) should be copied into newly saved session; false otherwise */
574 bool copy_external; /* true if external media should be consolidated into the newly saved session; false otherwise */
575
576 std::string final_session_folder_name; /* filled in by * Session::save_as(), provides full path to newly saved session */
577
578 /* emitted as we make progress. 3 arguments passed to signal
579 * handler:
580 *
581 * 1: percentage complete measured as a fraction (0-1.0) of
582 * total data copying done.
583 * 2: number of files copied so far
584 * 3: total number of files to copy
585 *
586 * Handler should return true for save-as to continue, or false
587 * to stop (and remove all evidence of partial save-as).
588 */
589 PBD::Signal<bool(float,int64_t,int64_t)> Progress;
590
591 /* if save_as() returns non-zero, this string will indicate the reason why.
592 */
593 std::string failure_message;
594 };

676 class StateProtector {
677 public:
678 StateProtector (Session* s) : _session (s) {
679 PBD::atomic_inc (s->_suspend_save);
680 }
681 ~StateProtector () {
682 if (PBD::atomic_dec_and_test (_session->_suspend_save)) {
683 while (_session->_save_queued) {
684 _session->_save_queued = false;
685 _session->save_state ("");
686 }
687 while (_session->_save_queued_pending) {
688 _session->_save_queued_pending = false;
689 _session->save_state ("", true);
690 }
691 }
692 }
693 private:
694 Session * _session;
695 };
